	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=1496&amp;mid=98538480931866">Strategy for Deepwaters</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=1496&amp;mid=98538480931866#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Fri, Mar 23rd 5:00 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.40]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok I just got my opalline helm for the quest about 15 minutes ago and here's what I did.&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all I am actually a bard, and lvl 40 so to the lvl 40 wizzy who couldn't get it I say, go camp something for your own class buddo.  But here's the deal there are 4 corner goblins and some middle ones.  Try to pull a corner one and you get two.  That's the smallest pull you can get as a bard by yourself.  Now heres the problem you have to pull two melee type goblins.  In other words noncasters.  If you get a caster just zone and try another corner.  I REALLY hope you have your tamborine by now because you are going to be using percussion based DOT songs to kill them, not to mention the 23% speed increase helps too.<br/><br/>So you pulled your two goblins, cast an initial chant of flame(lvl 38 song) and curtain(forget lvl but well before 30).  I say these two because they stack.  And then run as far away from the goblins as you can until they wear off.  Because those goblins have bows and arrows, and on top of that the arrows stun you!!  Gee verant I wish I could stun mobs with 1dmg arrows fired by a hunting bow.  Find some very "hilly" terrain to fight them at.  Near the derv camp by the south ro zone works well.  I say this because if you are on the other side of a hill then the goblins can't hit you with their arrows, but you can still hit them with your dot songs.  If you have done a lot of bard soloing in the past, ya know the good ole charm one...dot the other...repeat and rinse, then this should be cake to you because you are only weaving 3 songs and focussing on one mob.<br/><br/>Anyways you get the general idea.  Its very do-able once you have your 38 DOT song.  But unless you solo a lot and need the charisma for your charming I suggest save yourself the grief and buy a Skull Shaped Barbute for 200pp which puts this helm to shame.<br/><br/>Lioneil Winterwind<br/>40 Bard on Bristlebane</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
